    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>An Architect Objects</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter from Peter Samton, an architect, takes offense at use of term 'architect of the crime' in June 1 article on the Wendy's massacre</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In ''An Atrocity's Mystery of Evil'' (news article, June 1), your reference to John Taylor, a suspect in the Wendy's massacre, as the person ''who is thought to have been the architect of the crime'' is a most unfortunate analogy that many in my profession would take issue with.</p>
        <p>PETER SAMTON  New York, June 2, 2000</p>
        <p>The writer is a partner in an architectural firm.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
